  "prompt": "What are the entry requirements for the University of Melbourne?",
  "response": "The University of Melbourne is one of Australia's leading universities, and its entry requirements can vary depending on the level of study (undergraduate, postgraduate, etc.) and the specific course or program you are applying for. Here are general guidelines for entry requirements:\n\n---\n\n### **Undergraduate Entry Requirements**:\n1. **Academic Qualifications**:\n   - Successful completion of a recognized secondary school qualification (e.g., VCE in Victoria, IB, A-Levels, or equivalent).\n   - Meeting the minimum ATAR (Australian Tertiary Admission Rank) or equivalent for the course you\u2019re applying to (e.g., some courses require an ATAR of 85+, while others may require 95+).\n\n2. **English Language Proficiency**:\n   - For non-native English speakers, proof of English proficiency is required (e.g., IELTS, TOEFL, PTE Academic, or equivalent).\n   - Minimum scores typically include:\n     - IELTS: 6.5 (no band less than 6.0)\n     - TOEFL iBT: 79 (Writing: 21, Speaking: 18, Reading & Listening: 13)\n     - PTE Academic: 58 (no communicative skill below 50)\n\n3. **Subject Prerequisites**:\n   - Some courses may require specific subjects or prior knowledge in certain areas (e.g., Mathematics for Engineering, Chemistry for Biomedicine).\n\n4. **Additional Requirements**:\n   - Some courses may require interviews, portfolios, or auditions (e.g., Fine Arts, Music, or Design).\n\n---\n\n### **Postgraduate Entry Requirements**:\n1. **Academic Qualifications**:\n   - A recognized bachelor\u2019s degree or equivalent from an accredited institution.\n   - Minimum GPA or equivalent (varies by program; competitive programs may require a high GPA).\n\n2. **English Language Proficiency**:\n   - Similar to undergraduate requirements, but some programs may have higher score requirements.\n\n3. **Specific Program Requirements**:\n   - Some programs may require work experience, a statement of purpose, letters of recommendation, or a portfolio.\n\n4. **Standardized Tests**:\n   - Some programs (e.g., MBA) may require GMAT or GRE scores.\n\n---\n\n### **Other Considerations**:\n- **Scholarships**: Some scholarships have additional eligibility criteria.\n- **Visa Requirements**: International students must meet Australian student visa requirements.\n- **Additional Documents**: Some courses may require a personal statement, CV, or interview.\n\n---\n\n### **How to Apply**:\n- **Undergraduate**: Apply through the Victorian Tertiary Admissions Centre (VTAC) for domestic students or directly for international students.\n- **Postgraduate**: Apply directly to the University of Melbourne.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, visit the University of Melbourne\u2019s official website: [https://www.unimelb.edu.au](https://www.unimelb.edu.au).",
  "temperature": 1.0,
